<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Chickpea Salad Sandwich</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 can (15 oz) chickpeas, drained and rinsed</li>
            <li>1/4 cup vegan mayonnaise</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon Dijon mustard</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons red onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons celery, finely chopped</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon lemon juice</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon garlic powder</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>4 slices whole grain bread</li>
            <li>Lettuce leaves, tomato slices, and avocado slices for assembling</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, mash the chickpeas with a fork or potato masher until chunky.</li>
            <li>Add vegan mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, red onion, celery, fresh parsley, lemon juice, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper to the mashed chickpeas. Mix well to combine.</li>
            <li>Toast the slices of whole grain bread if desired.</li>
            <li>Assemble the sandwiches by placing a generous portion of the chickpea salad on a slice of bread.</li>
            <li>Top with lettuce leaves, tomato slices, and avocado slices.</li>
            <li>Place another slice of bread on top to complete the sandwich.</li>
            <li>Cut the sandwiches in half if desired and serve.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your tasty Chickpea Salad Sandwich!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

